miscConds.notes:
Defendant shall pay supervisory fees to the Department of Corrections;
Defendant shall successfully complete any/all counseling, evaluations, assessments and follow-up as deemed necessary;
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample and pay surcharge;
Defendant shall report for fingerprinting and photos pursuant to Wis Stats 970.02(7) to room 15, lower level of the Courthouse.  Please call 920-236-4906 to schedule an appointment.  
Credit for 4 days if revoked.  
Early termination of probation, at agent's discretion, upon successful completion of conditions and no further law violations.
